From 8068d30d7310b75b8c2f505e7fa936e18cc8e07d Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: =?UTF-8?q?=C3=98yvind=20Harboe?= <oyvind.harboe@zylin.com>
Date: Sun, 29 Mar 2026 23:14:37 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 04/34] Add orfs_design(designs = DESIGNS, mock_openroad =
 "@mock-openroad//src/bin:openroad") macro and auto-generated targets from
 config.mk
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

config.mk is the single source of truth for design configuration.
A repository rule parses all config.mk files and generates a DESIGNS
dict. Each design's BUILD.bazel calls orfs_design(designs = DESIGNS, mock_openroad = "@mock-openroad//src/bin:openroad") which creates
orfs_flow() targets with properly routed stage arguments.

Key components:
- bazel/designs.bzl: repo rule that watches config.mk files via
  repository_ctx.read() and re-parses on changes
- bazel/orfs.bzl: orfs_design(designs = DESIGNS, mock_openroad = "@mock-openroad//src/bin:openroad") macro with BLOCKS support, label
  filtering for Tier 2 designs, rules-base.json auto-detection
- MODULE.bazel: local bazel-orfs, docker image for yosys/klayout,
  local scripts/PDKs, configurable variables_yaml

Incremental caching verified: changing CORE_UTILIZATION rebuilds only
floorplan+place (2 actions), synthesis is cached (11 cache hits).

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
Signed-off-by: Øyvind Harboe <oyvind.harboe@zylin.com>
